timetraveller (1.0.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * GUI: Reindex button on the Archives panel for archives that are
    missing their .idx.zst sidecar. Launches the worker as a detached
    process (its own session group) so the long-running reindex
    survives a GUI exit. The label changes to "Indexing now" while a
    reindex is in flight, restored to the idle warning on completion
    (success refreshes the archive listing and re-selects the archive;
    failure pops a modal with the log tail and re-offers the button
    for retry). Per-(plan, archive) pid/log/done state files under
    XDG_STATE_HOME let a fresh GUI session adopt a still-running
    reindex launched by a prior session. Failed archives (status =
    "failed") are explicitly carved out — the archive file is at
    `.failed` suffix on disk and the worker's --reindex would not
    find it; those entries show "backup failed; archive incomplete"
    with no button.
  * GUI: cross-archive file search in the Archives panel. A new
    "Search files…" button toggles the right pane from the per-archive
    file tree to a grouped search-results view. Each matching file
    path becomes a top-level row; under it, one row per archive that
    contains a copy, with size and mtime-at-backup so the user can
    pick the right version to restore. Streaming sidecar scan with a
    bytes-level case-folded substring prefilter keeps the search
    sub-second per million-entry sidecar; results are off-thread in a
    QThread worker. Min 3 chars, capped at 500 distinct paths.
    Activating a version row exits search, selects the archive on the
    left, and scrolls the file tree to the path so Extract is one
    click away.

 -- Kim McCann <amplogik@gmail.com>  Sun, 31 May 2026 20:51:00 -0700

timetraveller (1.0.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New --finalize-archive action for post-crash manifest fix-up. When a
    backup run crashes between archive-write and manifest-save (e.g. a
    desktop crash during sidecar generation on a large full), the archive
    file itself is intact but the manifest entry stays in 'in-progress'
    with no date_finished, has_sidecar, has_frames, or size_bytes. The
    new action backfills those fields from what's on disk: status from
    --status (default 'ok-with-warnings'), date_finished=now, size_bytes
    from stat, has_sidecar/has_frames from sidecar presence. Pair with
    --reindex first if the .idx.zst sidecar also needs regenerating.
    --force allows overwriting an entry that already has a terminal
    status (otherwise refused as a typo-guard).

 -- Kim McCann <amplogik@gmail.com>  Sun, 31 May 2026 19:45:00 -0700

timetraveller (1.0.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * System-class plans are now plural. A new "homes" default plan backs up
    every user's /home tree as root via the same pkexec routing path used by
    the "system" plan. The worker, pkexec helper allowlists, and GUI config
    discovery all switched from a literal plan_name == "system" check to a
    SYSTEM_PLAN_NAMES set ({"system", "homes"}). The "home" default now
    resolves to the invoking user's actual /home/$USER instead of the
    misleading /home tree.
  * GUI can now save system-class plans without manual root edits. A new
    libexec helper (timetraveller-write-system-config) + polkit policy
    accepts the plan YAML on stdin, validates shape and plan-name, and
    writes atomically to /etc/timetraveller/<plan>.yaml. The previous
    "edit it as root" punt is replaced by a single pkexec auth prompt.
  * Plan list in the GUI now flags system-class plans (those routed through
    pkexec) with a warning-orange foreground and a "requires admin auth"
    tooltip to distinguish them from user-crontab plans.
  * .deb now seeds /etc/timetraveller/system.yaml and /etc/timetraveller/
    homes.yaml as conffiles, generated at build time from the factory
    defaults. First-launch users see the two system-class plans pre-listed.
  * Schedule panel layout cleanup: the "Full backup" section header now sits
    above the Schedule mode (Weekly/Monthly) radio so it's visually clear
    that the mode picks the Full backup cadence. Both "Full backup" and
    "Incremental backup" headers render bold + ~13pt with vertical breathing
    room so they're easy to spot as section dividers, not just labels.

 -- Kim McCann <amplogik@gmail.com>  Thu, 21 May 2026 10:00:00 -0700

timetraveller (1.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix system-plan --install-schedule under the .deb install.
    The pkexec helper only accepted /usr/local/bin/timetraveller-backup
    (the install.sh path); it now also accepts /usr/bin/timetraveller-backup
    (the .deb path). The worker auto-detects which canonical path exists,
    and the GUI no longer passes a bogus --binary-path computed from the
    site-packages layout for system-plan installs.

 -- Kim McCann <amplogik@gmail.com>  Thu, 21 May 2026 09:00:00 -0700

timetraveller (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial 1.0 release.
    - Seekable pax+zstd archives with per-file random-access extraction
    - Plan types: Active (scheduled, with retention) and Archive (manual, keep_all)
    - GUI: Plan / Schedule / Archives tabs with switch and remove operations
    - CLI worker with full coverage: --kind, --prune, --extract, --verify,
      --reindex, --list-archives, --list-files, --show-mounts, --show-schedule,
      --install-schedule, --suspend-schedule, --resume-schedule, --remove-plan,
      --switch-to-archive, --switch-to-active
    - Polkit-mediated installation of the system plan's cron entries
    - Built-in Help / About dialog with task-oriented how-tos and search

